1. Purpose

The purpose of this Business Requirements Document (BRD) is to define the business objectives, functional requirements, user roles, operational workflows, and high-level business rules for the Clinora platform.

This document serves as the primary business reference for all stakeholders before detailed product design and software development begin.

2. Business Objective

Clinora aims to provide clinics with a unified cloud-based Healthcare Operating System that digitizes and simplifies daily clinical and administrative operations.

The platform will eliminate fragmented systems by integrating patient management, appointment scheduling, Electronic Medical Records (EMR), laboratory workflows, billing, payments, analytics, and future AI capabilities into one centralized platform.

3. Business Goals

The initial business goals are:

Digitize clinic operations
Reduce administrative workload
Improve patient experience
Improve doctor productivity
Centralize patient medical records
Simplify appointment scheduling
Enable online booking and payments
Improve laboratory workflow
Provide operational analytics
Build a scalable SaaS platform for multiple clinics

Future business goals include:

Marketing automation
Inventory management
Insurance integrations
Pharmacy management
AI-powered clinical assistance
Platform APIs for third-party integrations
