Clinic Admin	Manages one clinic
Reception	Handles appointments and billing
Doctor	Provides consultations
Laboratory	Manages diagnostic workflows
Patient	Books appointments and views records

A detailed permission matrix will be prepared in a separate document.

11. Multi-Tenant Requirements

The platform shall:

Support multiple clinics
Isolate clinic data
Allow independent branding
Support independent users
Support independent reporting
Support independent billing
Share common infrastructure securely
12. Non-Functional Requirements
Performance
Average API response time < 500 ms
Appointment booking < 2 seconds
Dashboard loading < 3 seconds
Availability
Target uptime: 99.9%
Security
JWT authentication
Role-based authorization
HTTPS only
Encrypted passwords
Audit logging
Secure file storage
Scalability

The platform shall support growth from:

1 clinic to 10,000+ clinics
100 patients/day to millions of records

without major architectural redesign.

13. Success Criteria

The MVP will be considered successful when:

Clinics can complete daily operations using Clinora.
Patients can independently book appointments.
Doctors can complete consultations digitally.
Lab reports are shared electronically.
Payments are tracked digitally.
Administrators can monitor clinic operations through dashboards.
14. Risks

Potential risks include:

User adoption challenges
Regulatory changes
Third-party integration failures
Internet connectivity issues
Data migration from legacy systems
Payment gateway downtime

Mitigation strategies will be defined during implementation planning.

15. Assumptions
Clinics have internet connectivity.
Users possess smartphones or computers.
Clinics are willing to transition from manual processes.
Cloud infrastructure is available.
Payment gateway providers are operational.
SMS and email providers are available.
